<h2>Play modes</h2>

<p>Play modes define the behavior of a <strong>sample channel</strong>. As said before, they are divided into two families: <strong>loop</strong> and <strong>one shot</strong>. Main features of <strong>loop modes</strong>:</p>

<ul>
<li>work only when the sequencer is running;</li>
<li>constrained to the sequencer's boundaries;</li>
<li>triggered manually: you can't record keypress/keyrelease actions on them.</li>
</ul>

<p>Main features of <strong>one shot modes</strong>:</p>

<ul>
<li>independent from the sequencer;</li>
<li>you can record actions on them.</li>
</ul>


