<h2>Sample channels with actions</h2>

<p>As soon as the channel in <strong>one shot</strong> mode has some actions recorded into it, the <strong>read actions</strong> button <img src="{{ url('img/docs/read-recs-button.png') }}" alt="Read recordings button" title="Read recordings button" class="inline" /> appears on the right. If you disable it, Giada no longer reads the actions for that channel. That's slightly different from the <strong>mute button</strong>, because you can still play the sample manually and hear it.</p>

<p>By default when you disable the "R" button the actions stop immediately. By checking the <em>treat recorded channels as loops</em> flag in the <a href="{{ url('documentation/show/configuration') }}">configuration</a> panel the actions will stop at the next first beat, as a channel in <strong>loop</strong> mode would do.</p>
